{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "BlossomField",
  "description": "Scene 2 - the instanced-density scene (scene ladder rung 2, REALTIME_3D P8 instancing at performable scale). A soft rolling terrain (node.grid_mesh 64x64 over 14x14 units -> node.push_mesh displaced by low-frequency node.simplex_field_2d -> node.make_triangles) is object 0 of one node.render_scene. node.scatter_on_mesh samples that same terrain area-weighted and emits Array<InstanceTransform> placements (align_to_normal, per-instance random scale 0.55..1.35) wired into object 1's instances_1, so a small lathed blossom (node.range -> array_math MirrorRamp/ScaleOffset -> combine_xy -> revolve_curve -> make_triangles, a procedural stand-in pending a designed low-poly flower) draws once per placement in the SAME shared-depth pass - flowers behind ridges hide correctly, and the one shadow-casting warm sun shadows terrain and instances alike (the shadow pass instances too, render_scene D11). density is THE lead performance card (0..1500 instances on a fader - the meadow fills and empties under the performer's hand); flowerScale and the camera orbit/tilt/distance round out the surface. Wind on the host terrain (Scene 1's gust machinery driving push_mesh/bend so rigid instances ride a moving ground) is the planned next iteration; v0 is the static-density baseline. Garden.json proved this wiring as a P4/P8 demo; this preset is its performable successor.",
